08/06/2010
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Fifteen people were injured, none seriously, on Tuesday (June 8th) in a bomb attack targeting a police bus in Istanbul.
The bomb exploded as the vehicle passed a hospital in the Kucukcekmece district, on the west side.
Authorities suspect it may have been activated by a remote control device.
Police officers are among the injured.
No group has claimed responsibility for the attack so far.
(Anadolu news agency, BBC, AP, Hurriyet, AFP - 08/06/10)
